 :tx/rationale "ADR-FOUNDATION-024: Braid as Learned Attention. The entire system — store, fitness, acquisition, projection, calibration — is one attention mechanism operating on datoms. The CLI is the projection head. Intelligence is attention allocation under uncertainty — everything else is instance. The store IS the key-value memory (QKV). The acquisition function IS the softmax. The ACP projection IS the output layer. The calibration loop IS backpropagation. The attention budget replaces the token budget: units are bits of useful surprise, not tokens. Surprisal × relevance × actionability. The CLI is the Markov blanket between store and LLM — a learned boundary that optimizes itself for maximum information transfer. The free energy principle applied to organizational epistemology."
